President Obama has declared a major disaster in California following an earthquake that began on April 4, 2010. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected area, specifically Imperial County. This aid will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Additionally, federal funding will be available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Sandy Coachman has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made in the future if requested by the state and deemed necessary based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.